.TH MONSTAR 5 "2026-07-13" "monstar" "File Formats Manual"
.SH NAME
monstar \- configuration and theme file format
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B monstar
reads configuration from
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/config
or, when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset, from
.IR $HOME/.config/monstar/config .
An alternate file may be selected with
.BR monstar (1)'s
.B \-\-config
option.
A missing or unreadable file produces the default configuration.
.SH SYNTAX
The file contains one
.I key = value
entry per line.
Leading and trailing horizontal whitespace is ignored.
Empty lines and lines whose first non-whitespace character is
.B #
are comments.
Unknown keys, malformed lines, and invalid values are reported and ignored;
the previous value or default remains in effect.
.PP
For example:
.EX
copy-highlight-duration = 200
font-family = Iosevka
font-size = 12.5
theme = light:Rose Pine Dawn,dark:Rose Pine
window-padding-x = 4,8
.EE
.SH RELOADING
Press
.B Ctrl+Shift+,
or send
.B SIGUSR1
to reload the configuration.
Overrides supplied with
.B \-o
are reapplied after the file is loaded.
.PP
Visual and interaction settings apply to the running window.
The
.BR command ,
.BR linux-cgroup ,
and
.B scrollback-limit
settings describe resources created at startup and do not replace or move an
existing child or resize existing scrollback storage.
.SH GENERAL SETTINGS
.TP
.BI app-id " = string"
Set the Wayland app-id and desktop-entry hint.
The default is
.BR dev.rockorager.monstar .
.TP
.BI command " = command"
Set the child command used when no command is supplied on the command line.
An unprefixed value, or one prefixed with
.BR shell: ,
is passed to
.BR /bin/sh " " \-c .
A value prefixed with
.B direct:
is split on spaces and tabs and executed directly; shell quoting is not
interpreted in direct mode.
When unset,
.B SHELL
and then
.B /bin/sh
are used.
.TP
.BI linux-cgroup " = never|always"
Choose whether each newly spawned child is moved into a separate transient
systemd scope.
The default is
.BR never .
With
.BR always ,
Monstar falls back to its inherited cgroup if the session bus or systemd scope
creation is unavailable.
.TP
.BI pipe-command-output " = command"
Set a shell command that receives the last OSC 133-delimited command output on
standard input when
.B Ctrl+Shift+G
is pressed.
The default is unset.
.SH FONT SETTINGS
.TP
.BI font-family " = family"
Set the primary font family requested from fontconfig.
The default is
.BR monospace .
.TP
.BI font-size " = size[pt|px]"
Set the font size.
Bare values and
.B pt
values are typographic points;
.B px
values are logical pixels before Wayland output scaling.
Fractional values greater than zero and no greater than 512 are accepted.
The default is
.BR 12pt ,
equivalent to 16 logical pixels at 96 DPI.
.SH WINDOW SETTINGS
.TP
.BI background-opacity " = opacity"
Set the opacity of cells using the default terminal background.
The value is between 0 and 1 inclusive; the default is 1.
Explicit cell backgrounds, selections, cursors, text, and terminal graphics
retain their own opacity.
.TP
.BI window-padding-x " = pixels[,pixels]"
Set minimum left and right padding in logical pixels.
One value applies to both sides; two values set left and right independently.
The default is zero.
.TP
.BI window-padding-y " = pixels[,pixels]"
Set minimum top and bottom padding in logical pixels.
One value applies to both sides; two values set top and bottom independently.
The default is zero.
.SH STORAGE AND INPUT SETTINGS
.TP
.BI copy-highlight-duration " = milliseconds"
Set how long copied selections flash.
The default is 200 milliseconds.
Zero disables the flash.
.TP
.BI image-storage-limit " = bytes"
Set the kitty graphics image-data limit per terminal screen.
The default is 320000000 bytes and the maximum is 4294967295.
Zero disables the kitty graphics protocol.
.TP
.BI mouse-scroll-multiplier " = multiplier"
Apply one multiplier to both precision-device and discrete-wheel scrolling.
Finite values are clamped to the range 0.01 through 10000.
.TP
.BI mouse-scroll-multiplier " = precision:value,discrete:value"
Set the two scrolling multipliers independently.
Either named component may be updated without changing the other.
The defaults are
.B precision:1
and
.BR discrete:3 .
.TP
.BI scrollback-limit " = bytes"
Set the terminal page-storage limit, including the active screen.
The default is 50000000 bytes.
.SH THEME SELECTION
.TP
.BI theme " = name"
Use one named theme in both light and dark desktop color schemes.
.TP
.BI theme " = light:name,dark:name"
Use separate named themes and follow the desktop color-scheme portal.
Both sides are required.
.PP
An absolute theme path is read directly.
A theme name cannot contain path separators and is searched in this order:
.IP 1. 3
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/themes/name
or
.IR $HOME/.config/monstar/themes/name .
.IP 2. 3
.I $MONSTAR_RESOURCES_DIR/themes/name
when
.B MONSTAR_RESOURCES_DIR
is set.
.IP 3. 3
The installed
.I share/monstar/themes/name
directory relative to the Monstar executable.
.PP
Monstar installs Ghostty's iTerm2 theme collection.
Without a
.B theme
setting, the built-in Radix-based light and dark themes follow the desktop
color scheme.
.SH COLOR SETTINGS
Colors use six hexadecimal RGB digits, with an optional leading
.BR # .
For example,
.B #ffe629
and
.B ffe629
are equivalent.
.PP
An explicit color in the main configuration overrides the named theme.
Runtime OSC color changes may override terminal, cursor, and selection colors
until they are reset by the application.
.TP
.BI background " = color"
Set the default terminal background.
Built-in defaults are
.B #f0f0f3
in light mode and
.B #212225
in dark mode.
.TP
.BI copy-highlight " = color"
Set the temporary background shown after a selection is copied.
The built-in default is Radix Yellow 9,
.BR #ffe629 ,
in both color schemes.
.TP
.BI copy-highlight-foreground " = color"
Set text shown during the post-copy flash.
The built-in default is
.B #1c2024
in both color schemes.
.TP
.BI cursor-color " = color"
Set the cursor color.
Built-in defaults are
.B #1c2024
in light mode and
.B #edeeef
in dark mode.
.TP
.BI cursor-text " = color"
Set text beneath a focused block cursor.
When unset, the terminal background is used.
.TP
.BI foreground " = color"
Set the default terminal foreground.
Built-in defaults are
.B #1c2024
in light mode and
.B #edeeef
in dark mode.
.TP
.BI palette " = index=color"
Override one terminal palette entry.
The index must be between 0 and 255 and may use decimal or a
.BR 0b ,
.BR 0o ,
or
.B 0x
numeric prefix.
Repeat the setting to override multiple entries.
.TP
.BI selection-background " = color"
Set the selection background.
Built-in defaults are
.B #c2e5ff
in light mode and
.B #104d87
in dark mode.
.TP
.BI selection-foreground " = color"
Set selected text.
Built-in defaults are
.B #1c2024
in light mode and
.B #edeeef
in dark mode.
.SH THEME FILES
Theme files use the same line syntax as the main configuration but accept only
these color keys:
.BR background ,
.BR copy-highlight ,
.BR copy-highlight-foreground ,
.BR cursor-color ,
.BR cursor-text ,
.BR foreground ,
.BR palette ,
.BR selection-background ,
and
.BR selection-foreground .
The
.B palette
key may be repeated.
.PP
Main-configuration colors override theme-file colors.
Palette entries not supplied by either use the built-in palette.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Fallback base directory when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.B MONSTAR_RESOURCES_DIR
Resource directory searched for installed themes.
.TP
.B SHELL
Default child command when
.B command
is unset.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the default configuration and user themes.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/monstar/config
Fallback configuration file.
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/monstar/themes/
Fallback user theme directory.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/config
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/themes/
User theme directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR monstar (1)
